(2)starting entity: The starting entity is also called salient entity, and the salient entity is the root change that causes the modification of the rest of entities in a change set, while the rest of entities are the dependency modification along with the salient one.
You will be presented with a starting entity and tools (functions) will be provided to access the more information of the origin system. Your task is to gradually explain which entity really need to be synchronized, based on the starting entity and the information obtained through the function-call. 10. `EuropeanAIPlayer.java` - 6 supports, confidence 0.017

These entities seem to be closely related to `Unit.java` because they have high support counts and relatively high confidence values. This suggests that when `Unit.java` was changed, these files often needed modifications as well.

To further understand the relationships between `Unit.java` and these other entities, we could look at how they interact or depend on each other. To do this, we can use the `get_coupling_dependencies` function to get more detailed information about the types of coupling between them.
